#Title#
Hippias summary
#Content#
Hippias about 460 BC - about 400 BC Hippias was a Greek contemporary of Socrates whose only contribution to mathematics seems to be the quadratrix - a curve he may have used for squaring the circle and trisecting angles. Go to the full MacTutor biography
